108. 1. quam ποιότητα Graeci vocant. Cicero adds this remark because the Greek word was quite familiar to his readers, but the Latin word was first coined by himself, as he says Acad. 1, 6, 24, where he reck- ons it among the verbis inauditis. The Greek ποιότης too was first coined by Plato, as is remarked in his life in XVestermann’s Biogr., p. 393, as well as in other places. The word occurs in Theaet., p. 182 A, where Plato him- self calls it an ἀλλόκοτον ὄνομα.
